HEADWORD: Metatungstic
<hw>Met`a*tung"stic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>meta-</ets> + <ets>tungstic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid known only in its salts
(the <xex>metatungstates</xex>) and properly called
<xex>polytungstic</xex>, or <xex>pyrotungstic</xex>, acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

